{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1087,"text":"There is something about physics"},{"time":5296,"text":"that has been really bothering me\nsince I was a little kid."},{"time":11010,"text":"And it's related to a question"},{"time":12843,"text":"that scientists have been asking\nfor almost 100 years,"},{"time":16111,"text":"with no answer."},{"time":19108,"text":"How do the smallest things in nature,"},{"time":22142,"text":"the particles of the quantum world,"},{"time":24319,"text":"match up with the largest\nthings in nature --"},{"time":27374,"text":"planets and stars and galaxies\nheld together by gravity?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31250,"text":"As a kid, I would puzzle\nover questions just like this."},{"time":34047,"text":"I would fiddle around\nwith microscopes and electromagnets,"},{"time":36963,"text":"and I would read\nabout the forces of the small"},{"time":39182,"text":"and about quantum mechanics"},{"time":40540,"text":"and I would marvel at how well\nthat description matched up"},{"time":44128,"text":"to our observation."},{"time":46220,"text":"Then I would look at the stars,"},{"time":47827,"text":"and I would read about how well\nwe understand gravity,"},{"time":50375,"text":"and I would think surely,\nthere must be some elegant way"},{"time":53749,"text":"that these two systems match up."},{"time":57021,"text":"But there's not."},{"time":59673,"text":"And the books would say,"},{"time":60857,"text":"yeah, we understand a lot\nabout these two realms separately,"},{"time":64064,"text":"but when we try to link\nthem mathematically,"},{"time":66698,"text":"everything breaks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68674,"text":"And for 100 years,"},{"time":70008,"text":"none of our ideas as to how to solve\nthis basically physics disaster,"},{"time":75060,"text":"has ever been supported by evidence."},{"time":78271,"text":"And to little old me --"},{"time":79949,"text":"little, curious, skeptical James --"},{"time":81783,"text":"this was a supremely unsatisfying answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86011,"text":"So, I'm still a skeptical little kid."},{"time":88268,"text":"Flash-forward now\nto December of 2015,"},{"time":93029,"text":"when I found myself smack in the middle"},{"time":95527,"text":"of the physics world\nbeing flipped on its head."},{"time":99999,"text":"It all started when we at CERN\nsaw something intriguing in our data:"},{"time":103343,"text":"a hint of a new particle,"},{"time":105641,"text":"an inkling of a possibly extraordinary\nanswer to this question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111777,"text":"So I'm still a skeptical\nlittle kid, I think,"},{"time":113928,"text":"but I'm also now a particle hunter."},{"time":116085,"text":"I am a physicist at CERN's\nLarge Hadron Collider,"},{"time":119572,"text":"the largest science\nexperiment ever mounted."},{"time":123877,"text":"It's a 27-kilometer tunnel\non the border of France and Switzerland"},{"time":127436,"text":"buried 100 meters underground."},{"time":129310,"text":"And in this tunnel,"},{"time":130488,"text":"we use superconducting magnets\ncolder than outer space"},{"time":134465,"text":"to accelerate protons\nto almost the speed of light"},{"time":137550,"text":"and slam them into each other\nmillions of times per second,"},{"time":141451,"text":"collecting the debris of these collisions"},{"time":144301,"text":"to search for new, undiscovered\nfundamental particles."},{"time":148727,"text":"Its design and construction\ntook decades of work"},{"time":151215,"text":"by thousands of physicists\nfrom around the globe,"},{"time":154271,"text":"and in the summer of 2015,"},{"time":156836,"text":"we had been working tirelessly\nto switch on the LHC"},{"time":160284,"text":"at the highest energy that humans\nhave ever used in a collider experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165735,"text":"Now, higher energy is important"},{"time":168282,"text":"because for particles,\nthere is an equivalence"},{"time":170493,"text":"between energy and particle mass,"},{"time":172718,"text":"and mass is just a number\nput there by nature."},{"time":176068,"text":"To discover new particles,"},{"time":177410,"text":"we need to reach these bigger numbers."},{"time":179556,"text":"And to do that, we have to build\na bigger, higher energy collider,"},{"time":182834,"text":"and the biggest, highest\nenergy collider in the world"},{"time":185423,"text":"is the Large Hadron Collider."},{"time":188271,"text":"And then, we collide protons\nquadrillions of times,"},{"time":193194,"text":"and we collect this data very slowly,\nover months and months."},{"time":198813,"text":"And then new particles might show up\nin our data as bumps --"},{"time":203172,"text":"slight deviations from what you expect,"},{"time":205641,"text":"little clusters of data points\nthat make a smooth line not so smooth."},{"time":210379,"text":"For example, this bump,"},{"time":213010,"text":"after months of data-taking in 2012,"},{"time":215567,"text":"led to the discovery\nof the Higgs particle --"},{"time":217720,"text":"the Higgs boson --"},{"time":218949,"text":"and to a Nobel Prize\nfor the confirmation of its existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223972,"text":"This jump up in energy in 2015"},{"time":228628,"text":"represented the best chance\nthat we as a species had ever had"},{"time":231944,"text":"of discovering new particles --"},{"time":233445,"text":"new answers to these\nlong-standing questions,"},{"time":235581,"text":"because it was almost\ntwice as much energy as we used"},{"time":238702,"text":"when we discovered the Higgs boson."},{"time":240648,"text":"Many of my colleagues had been working\ntheir entire careers for this moment,"},{"time":244413,"text":"and frankly, to little curious me,"},{"time":246513,"text":"this was the moment\nI'd been waiting for my entire life."},{"time":249447,"text":"So 2015 was go time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252654,"text":"So June 2015,"},{"time":255722,"text":"the LHC is switched back on."},{"time":259040,"text":"My colleagues and I held our breath\nand bit our fingernails,"},{"time":261941,"text":"and then finally we saw\nthe first proton collisions"},{"time":264476,"text":"at this highest energy ever."},{"time":266456,"text":"Applause, champagne, celebration."},{"time":268556,"text":"This was a milestone for science,"},{"time":272176,"text":"and we had no idea what we would find\nin this brand-new data."},{"time":279990,"text":"And then a few weeks later,\nwe found a bump."},{"time":284192,"text":"It wasn't a very big bump,"},{"time":286952,"text":"but it was big enough to make\nyou raise your eyebrow."},{"time":289488,"text":"But on a scale of one to 10\nfor eyebrow raises,"},{"time":291763,"text":"if 10 indicates that you've\ndiscovered a new particle,"},{"time":294397,"text":"this eyebrow raise is about a four."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296148,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298432,"text":"I spent hours, days, weeks\nin secret meetings,"},{"time":303667,"text":"arguing with my colleagues\nover this little bump,"},{"time":306051,"text":"poking and prodding it with our most\nruthless experimental sticks"},{"time":309311,"text":"to see if it would withstand scrutiny."},{"time":311988,"text":"But even after months\nof working feverishly --"},{"time":315473,"text":"sleeping in our offices\nand not going home,"},{"time":317929,"text":"candy bars for dinner,"},{"time":320030,"text":"coffee by the bucketful --"},{"time":321624,"text":"physicists are machines\nfor turning coffee into diagrams --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":325891,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":327314,"text":"This little bump would not go away."},{"time":330704,"text":"So after a few months,"},{"time":332866,"text":"we presented our little bump to the world\nwith a very clear message:"},{"time":337457,"text":"this little bump is interesting\nbut it's not definitive,"},{"time":340192,"text":"so let's keep an eye on it\nas we take more data."},{"time":343872,"text":"So we were trying to be\nextremely cool about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347463,"text":"And the world ran with it anyway."},{"time":350383,"text":"The news loved it."},{"time":352735,"text":"People said it reminded\nthem of the little bump"},{"time":355314,"text":"that was shown on the way\ntoward the Higgs boson discovery."},{"time":358761,"text":"Better than that,\nmy theorist colleagues --"},{"time":362548,"text":"I love my theorist colleagues --"},{"time":364889,"text":"my theorist colleagues wrote\n500 papers about this little bump."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368525,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370574,"text":"The world of particle physics\nhad been flipped on its head."},{"time":375745,"text":"But what was it about this particular bump"},{"time":380011,"text":"that caused thousands of physicists\nto collectively lose their cool?"},{"time":385596,"text":"This little bump was unique."},{"time":388198,"text":"This little bump indicated"},{"time":389591,"text":"that we were seeing an unexpectedly\nlarge number of collisions"},{"time":392637,"text":"whose debris consisted\nof only two photons,"},{"time":395992,"text":"two particles of light."},{"time":397260,"text":"And that's rare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399069,"text":"Particle collisions are not\nlike automobile collisions."},{"time":401713,"text":"They have different rules."},{"time":403256,"text":"When two particles collide\nat almost the speed of light,"},{"time":405930,"text":"the quantum world takes over."},{"time":407375,"text":"And in the quantum world,"},{"time":408659,"text":"these two particles\ncan briefly create a new particle"},{"time":411876,"text":"that lives for a tiny fraction of a second"},{"time":414680,"text":"before splitting into other particles\nthat hit our detector."},{"time":417585,"text":"Imagine a car collision\nwhere the two cars vanish upon impact,"},{"time":421014,"text":"a bicycle appears in their place --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423307,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424402,"text":"And then that bicycle explodes\ninto two skateboards,"},{"time":426887,"text":"which hit our detector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428092,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":429495,"text":"Hopefully, not literally."},{"time":431472,"text":"They're very expensive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434191,"text":"Events where only two photons\nhit out detector are very rare."},{"time":437963,"text":"And because of the special\nquantum properties of photons,"},{"time":441709,"text":"there's a very small number\nof possible new particles --"},{"time":445521,"text":"these mythical bicycles --"},{"time":447042,"text":"that can give birth to only two photons."},{"time":449812,"text":"But one of these options is huge,"},{"time":452672,"text":"and it has to do with\nthat long-standing question"},{"time":455532,"text":"that bothered me as a tiny little kid,"},{"time":458078,"text":"about gravity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461946,"text":"Gravity may seem super strong to you,"},{"time":464642,"text":"but it's actually crazily weak\ncompared to the other forces of nature."},{"time":468766,"text":"I can briefly beat gravity when I jump,"},{"time":472390,"text":"but I can't pick a proton out of my hand."},{"time":476463,"text":"The strength of gravity compared\nto the other forces of nature?"},{"time":480480,"text":"It's 10 to the minus 39."},{"time":482694,"text":"That's a decimal with 39 zeros after it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485255,"text":"Worse than that,"},{"time":486436,"text":"all of the other known forces of nature\nare perfectly described"},{"time":489487,"text":"by this thing we call the Standard Model,"},{"time":491548,"text":"which is our current best description\nof nature at its smallest scales,"},{"time":495007,"text":"and quite frankly,"},{"time":496187,"text":"one of the most successful\nachievements of humankind --"},{"time":500388,"text":"except for gravity, which is absent\nfrom the Standard Model."},{"time":504424,"text":"It's crazy."},{"time":506046,"text":"It's almost as though most\nof gravity has gone missing."},{"time":510394,"text":"We feel a little bit of it,"},{"time":512085,"text":"but where's the rest of it?"},{"time":513785,"text":"No one knows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516003,"text":"But one theoretical explanation\nproposes a wild solution."},{"time":522120,"text":"You and I --"},{"time":523483,"text":"even you in the back --"},{"time":525085,"text":"we live in three dimensions of space."},{"time":527254,"text":"I hope that's a\nnon-controversial statement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529835,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531688,"text":"All of the known particles also live\nin three dimensions of space."},{"time":535150,"text":"In fact, a particle is just another name"},{"time":537364,"text":"for an excitation\nin a three-dimensional field;"},{"time":540397,"text":"a localized wobbling in space."},{"time":543288,"text":"More importantly, all the math\nthat we use to describe all this stuff"},{"time":546841,"text":"assumes that there are only\nthree dimensions of space."},{"time":549938,"text":"But math is math, and we can play\naround with our math however we want."},{"time":553343,"text":"And people have been playing around\nwith extra dimensions of space"},{"time":556533,"text":"for a very long time,"},{"time":557712,"text":"but it's always been an abstract\nmathematical concept."},{"time":560321,"text":"I mean, just look around you --\nyou at the back, look around --"},{"time":563517,"text":"there's clearly only\nthree dimensions of space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566954,"text":"But what if that's not true?"},{"time":570109,"text":"What if the missing gravity is leaking\ninto an extra-spatial dimension"},{"time":576388,"text":"that's invisible to you and I?"},{"time":579355,"text":"What if gravity is just as strong\nas the other forces"},{"time":582473,"text":"if you were to view it in this\nextra-spatial dimension,"},{"time":585638,"text":"and what you and I experience\nis a tiny slice of gravity"},{"time":588562,"text":"make it seem very weak?"},{"time":592158,"text":"If this were true,"},{"time":593357,"text":"we would have to expand\nour Standard Model of particles"},{"time":596129,"text":"to include an extra particle,\na hyperdimensional particle of gravity,"},{"time":600239,"text":"a special graviton that lives\nin extra-spatial dimensions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603258,"text":"I see the looks on your faces."},{"time":604747,"text":"You should be asking me the question,"},{"time":606590,"text":"\"How in the world are we going to test\nthis crazy, science fiction idea,"},{"time":610258,"text":"stuck as we are in three dimensions?\""},{"time":612773,"text":"The way we always do,"},{"time":614079,"text":"by slamming together two protons --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616242,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617418,"text":"Hard enough that\nthe collision reverberates"},{"time":620006,"text":"into any extra-spatial dimensions\nthat might be there,"},{"time":622721,"text":"momentarily creating\nthis hyperdimensional graviton"},{"time":625344,"text":"that then snaps back\ninto the three dimensions of the LHC"},{"time":629748,"text":"and spits off two photons,"},{"time":632278,"text":"two particles of light."},{"time":635417,"text":"And this hypothetical,\nextra-dimensional graviton"},{"time":638351,"text":"is one of the only possible,\nhypothetical new particles"},{"time":642082,"text":"that has the special quantum properties"},{"time":644241,"text":"that could give birth to our little,\ntwo-photon bump."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"So, the possibility of explaining\nthe mysteries of gravity"},{"time":655844,"text":"and of discovering extra\ndimensions of space --"},{"time":659366,"text":"perhaps now you get a sense"},{"time":660982,"text":"as to why thousands of physics geeks\ncollectively lost their cool"},{"time":665130,"text":"over our little, two-photon bump."},{"time":667036,"text":"A discovery of this type\nwould rewrite the textbooks."},{"time":670739,"text":"But remember,"},{"time":671915,"text":"the message from us experimentalists"},{"time":673663,"text":"that actually were doing\nthis work at the time,"},{"time":675926,"text":"was very clear:"},{"time":677104,"text":"we need more data."},{"time":678302,"text":"With more data,"},{"time":679845,"text":"the little bump will either turn into\na nice, crisp Nobel Prize --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":683893,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":685677,"text":"Or the extra data will fill in\nthe space around the bump"},{"time":688665,"text":"and turn it into a nice, smooth line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691515,"text":"So we took more data,"},{"time":692757,"text":"and with five times the data,\nseveral months later,"},{"time":695358,"text":"our little bump"},{"time":697072,"text":"turned into a smooth line."},{"time":703217,"text":"The news reported on a \"huge\ndisappointment,\" on \"faded hopes,\""},{"time":706725,"text":"and on particle physicists \"being sad.\""},{"time":709259,"text":"Given the tone of the coverage,"},{"time":711094,"text":"you'd think that we had decided\nto shut down the LHC and go home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714606,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":716628,"text":"But that's not what we did."},{"time":721057,"text":"But why not?"},{"time":724475,"text":"I mean, if I didn't discover\na particle -- and I didn't --"},{"time":728209,"text":"if I didn't discover a particle,\nwhy am I here talking to you?"},{"time":731262,"text":"Why didn't I just hang my head in shame"},{"time":733723,"text":"and go home?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":739169,"text":"Particle physicists are explorers."},{"time":743421,"text":"And very much of what we do\nis cartography."},{"time":747468,"text":"Let me put it this way: forget\nabout the LHC for a second."},{"time":750344,"text":"Imagine you are a space explorer\narriving at a distant planet,"},{"time":753750,"text":"searching for aliens."},{"time":755099,"text":"What is your first task?"},{"time":757931,"text":"To immediately orbit the planet,\nland, take a quick look around"},{"time":761031,"text":"for any big, obvious signs of life,"},{"time":762941,"text":"and report back to home base."},{"time":764784,"text":"That's the stage we're at now."},{"time":767269,"text":"We took a first look at the LHC"},{"time":768780,"text":"for any new, big,\nobvious-to-spot particles,"},{"time":771088,"text":"and we can report that there are none."},{"time":773631,"text":"We saw a weird-looking alien bump\non a distant mountain,"},{"time":776328,"text":"but once we got closer,\nwe saw it was a rock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778816,"text":"But then what do we do?\nDo we just give up and fly away?"},{"time":781480,"text":"Absolutely not;"},{"time":782791,"text":"we would be terrible scientists if we did."},{"time":785120,"text":"No, we spend the next couple\nof decades exploring,"},{"time":788757,"text":"mapping out the territory,"},{"time":790261,"text":"sifting through the sand\nwith a fine instrument,"},{"time":792650,"text":"peeking under every stone,"},{"time":794132,"text":"drilling under the surface."},{"time":796106,"text":"New particles can either\nshow up immediately"},{"time":798723,"text":"as big, obvious-to-spot bumps,"},{"time":800880,"text":"or they can only reveal themselves\nafter years of data taking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806103,"text":"Humanity has just begun its exploration\nat the LHC at this big high energy,"},{"time":810537,"text":"and we have much searching to do."},{"time":812352,"text":"But what if, even after 10 or 20 years,\nwe still find no new particles?"},{"time":819053,"text":"We build a bigger machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820772,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":822370,"text":"We search at higher energies."},{"time":824476,"text":"We search at higher energies."},{"time":826946,"text":"Planning is already underway\nfor a 100-kilometer tunnel"},{"time":830612,"text":"that will collide particles\nat 10 times the energy of the LHC."},{"time":833612,"text":"We don't decide where\nnature places new particles."},{"time":836366,"text":"We only decide to keep exploring."},{"time":838036,"text":"But what if, even after\na 100-kilometer tunnel"},{"time":840618,"text":"or a 500-kilometer tunnel"},{"time":842502,"text":"or a 10,000-kilometer\ncollider floating in space"},{"time":845367,"text":"between the Earth and the Moon,"},{"time":846969,"text":"we still find no new particles?"},{"time":851597,"text":"Then perhaps we're doing\nparticle physics wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854315,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":856130,"text":"Perhaps we need to rethink things."},{"time":859127,"text":"Maybe we need more resources,\ntechnology, expertise"},{"time":862413,"text":"than what we currently have."},{"time":864610,"text":"We already use artificial intelligence\nand machine learning techniques"},{"time":867975,"text":"in parts of the LHC,"},{"time":869152,"text":"but imagine designing\na particle physics experiment"},{"time":871582,"text":"using such sophisticated algorithms"},{"time":873275,"text":"that it could teach itself to discover\na hyperdimensional graviton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876467,"text":"But what if?"},{"time":877648,"text":"What if the ultimate question:"},{"time":879117,"text":"What if even artificial intelligence\ncan't help us answer our questions?"},{"time":882614,"text":"What if these open questions,\nfor centuries,"},{"time":884749,"text":"are destined to be unanswered\nfor the foreseeable future?"},{"time":887442,"text":"What if the stuff that's bothered me\nsince I was a little kid"},{"time":890395,"text":"is destined to be unanswered\nin my lifetime?"},{"time":894395,"text":"Then that ..."},{"time":896282,"text":"will be even more fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900144,"text":"We will be forced to think\nin completely new ways."},{"time":904361,"text":"We'll have to go back to our assumptions,"},{"time":906443,"text":"and determine if there was\na flaw somewhere."},{"time":909401,"text":"And we'll need to encourage more people\nto join us in studying science"},{"time":912820,"text":"since we need fresh eyes\non these century-old problems."},{"time":915906,"text":"I don't have the answers,\nand I'm still searching for them."},{"time":919064,"text":"But someone -- maybe\nshe's in school right now,"},{"time":921417,"text":"maybe she's not even born yet --"},{"time":923783,"text":"could eventually guide us to see physics\nin a completely new way,"},{"time":926940,"text":"and to point out that perhaps\nwe're just asking the wrong questions."},{"time":932112,"text":"Which would not be the end of physics,"},{"time":934546,"text":"but a novel beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937204,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":938378,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}